tossup_question: -   –  Set q contains all irrational numbers r such that 0 < r < 1. Which of the following is true about q?
tossup_MCQoptions:
W) It is an empty set
X) It has a countably infinite number of elements
Y) It has an uncountably infinite number of elements
Z) It has a nonzero finite number of elements
tossup_answer: ANSWER: Y) IT HAS AN UNCOUNTABLY INFINITE NUMBER OF ELEMENTS
bonus_question: -   –  Consider a criminal trial in which the defendant is innocent until proven guilty. If the jury accepts the null hypothesis when the defendant is innocent, which of the following has occurred?
bonus_MCQoptions:
W) The jury made the right decision
X) The jury committed a type I error
Y) The jury committed a type II error
Z) The jury committed a type III error
bonus_answer: ANSWER: W) THE JURY MADE THE RIGHT DECISION
